<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Getting Started on Cloud Share</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/</link><description>Recent content in Getting Started on Cloud Share</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Installation</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/installation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/installation/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="installation"&gt;Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cloud Share consists of two .NET 10 global tools published to NuGet. Installation takes about two minutes on any platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites"&gt;Prerequisites &lt;a href="#prerequisites" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="net-10-sdk"&gt;.NET 10 SDK &lt;a href="#net-10-sdk" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Both tools require the &lt;strong&gt;.NET 10 SDK or Runtime&lt;/strong&gt;. Download it from &lt;a href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/10.0" rel="external" target="_blank"&gt;dot.net&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Quick Start</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/quickstart/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/quickstart/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="quick-start"&gt;Quick Start &lt;a href="#quick-start" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This guide walks you through your very first cloud-share transfer — from starting the sender to receiving and verifying a file on another machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ℹ️ Info:&lt;/strong&gt; You need two machines (or two terminal windows) to complete this walkthrough: one acting as the &lt;strong&gt;sender&lt;/strong&gt; and one as the &lt;strong&gt;receiver&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-1--start-the-sender"&gt;Step 1 — Start the sender &lt;a href="#step-1--start-the-sender" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;On the &lt;strong&gt;sending machine&lt;/strong&gt;, open a terminal and run:&lt;/p&gt;



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="a06bff3" class="language-bash "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;cloud-share-sender&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The sender will:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Core Concepts</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/concepts/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/concepts/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="core-concepts"&gt;Core Concepts &lt;a href="#core-concepts" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before diving into advanced features, it helps to understand the building blocks that make cloud-share work. This page explains each concept at a level that will inform how you use the tool day-to-day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="dev-tunnels"&gt;Dev Tunnels &lt;a href="#dev-tunnels" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Dev Tunnel&lt;/strong&gt; is an outbound HTTPS connection from the sender machine to Microsoft&amp;rsquo;s relay infrastructure. It creates a publicly accessible URL (e.g. &lt;code&gt;https://mtszwr0l.uks1.devtunnels.ms:5000&lt;/code&gt;) that proxies all requests back to the sender&amp;rsquo;s local port 5000.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>